<p>I'm trying to save object into serializable data field. I use ormlite and hsqldb.  ORMLite maps serializable field to BINARY (without length specified) type in hsqldb, by default BINARY type length is 1.</p>  <p>And when i try to save the object in the DB, i get an error:</p>  <pre><code>org.hsqldb.HsqlException: data exception: string data, right truncation;       table: "DBFORMS" column: "resultList" </code></pre>  <p>I also tried to set the size of the binary field using the width attribute, but without success.</p>  <p>Here is my field definition:</p>  <pre><code>@DatabaseField(width = 1024*1024, dataType = DataType.SERIALIZABLE) protected ArrayList&lt;ResultColumn&gt; resultList; </code></pre>  <p>HSQLdb definition: <code>"resultList" BINARY</code>.  Please advise.</p>